Rachel,

Following up on the Westfield submission. A question came up that I need
clarification on before we can bind:

The Oakbrook, IL location (Location 4 on the SOV — 38,000 sq ft, $4.2M
building value) has had one of its two anchor tenant spaces vacant since
November 2023. The space (approximately 14,000 sq ft, or about 37% of the
building) is actively being marketed and they expect to have a new tenant
signed by June 2024. There are two smaller inline tenants still occupying
the remainder of the building.

Questions:
  1. Does Pinnacle's policy form include a standard vacancy clause (e.g., 60-day)?
     If so, would the partial vacancy at Location 4 trigger any exclusions or
     conditions at this point?
  2. Is there anything we need to report or warrant on the application regarding
     this vacancy?
  3. Would Pinnacle consider a vacancy permit endorsement for that location while
     the space is being re-tenanted, and if so, at what additional premium?

Client is aware and wants to be fully transparent — they're not trying to hide
the situation, they just want to know their exposure before we bind.

Also: have you had a chance to get to the submission yet? We're hoping for an
indication by March 25th. The expiration is May 1st but the client likes to
have at least 30 days to review.

Thanks,
James

